Czech Shares Gain to Week High as Komercni, Telefonica Advance

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-08-17T15:20:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-17/czech-shares-drop-second-day-as-cez-komecni-banka-nwr-retreat.html
Czech shares climbed to the highest
in more than a week as Komecni Banka AS, New World Resources Plc
and Telefonica Czech Republic AS advanced.  The PX gauge of companies gained 1.7 percent to 1,022.2 at
the 4:28 p.m. end of trading in  Prague , the highest since Aug.
8. Komercni, a unit of Societe Generale SA with a 19 percent
weighting in the index, jumped 4.4 percent to 3,220 koruna.  Global equities advanced as commodities rose and companies
including Target Corp. and Staples Inc. published earnings that
beat analyst estimates. Mining companies and retailers led a
rebound in European shares.  NWR, the biggest Czech coking-coal producer, increased 1.5
percent to 171 koruna as  Europe ’s benchmark coal derivatives
rose 0.3 percent to 127.25 euros per metric ton in Amsterdam.
Telefonica added 1.4 percent to 403 koruna, paring the biggest
Czech phone operator’s 3 percent drop in the previous four days.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
